Took forever to get a bowl of soup and a skillet and the other tables already got their THIRD course and we’re finishing up. Waitress never stopped at our table but kept checking in on the other two. When she did ask how everything is, she said it as she was quickly walking by and didn’t look at us. We kept trying to get boxes and a check. We’ve been here three times before and never had such a poor experience. Probably won’t be coming back.

caption: I really like going to this laid back home style restaurant. The staff is always friendly, make you feel like they are so glad you came. The food is very good home style cooking comfort food. They have a varied menu with great prices. I love the pancake breakfast or hot turkey sandwich for lunch. My go to place for that regular homey style food that I remember.
Great little diner. Good food. Cozy environment. Portions are sizable. Decent staff. Mainly serves breakfast. Overall a good restaurant. 4/5 stars.

Was headed to a different place to eat breakfast and my spouse spotted this place from Western. We can't resist vintage diners, so changed our plans and turned around. The curtains, the vintage smell of old building, and the booths; we only hoped the food was good. I had a veggie skillet that was perfectly prepared and the spouse's pork chop sandwich looked awesome. The price is right, and the staff was very friendly.  A tip for parking: try the south side of Fullerton when the weather is clear of snow to save a couple bucks as it is pay and display on the north side of Fullerton.
